properties.abstract: This bike route in the middle on Toggenburg is quite challenging, but offers a unique far-reaching view as a reward. Both Lake Zrich and Lake Constance can be seen from the Chrzegg.
properties.description:
This route begins in Toggenburgs community centre, Wattwil. Right at the start there are 600m to be scaled before you can take a rest on the Chrzegg. The view from the alpine restaurant is unique; you can gaze over Lake Zrich and Lake Constance, the highlands of St Gallen and the Glarus, Central Swiss and Bernese Alps.

The route continues to the village of Libingen, where the former ski racer, Maria Walliser, learnt to ski. Following the ascent down the Chapf, the route leads down to the pretty village of Krinau in the valley (with only 300 inhabitants).

The last section takes you back to Wattwil along the Thur. Wattwil is easy to get to from Rapperswil, Wil and St Gallen.
